    • testBbox

      public void testBbox​(Node node)
      Tests the distance between the generated bbox points, it should be at least x2 the input distance in case of worst case scenario path (straight line). Therefore tests fail when the generated bbox is too small. Since it uses the haversine formula twice, which leads to a delta of 6%, and inaccuracies of the bounding box generating algorithm, a delta of 15% is used.
      Parameters:
      node - A position on the map to verify the bbox for.

    • testJson

      public void testJson() throws Exception
      Tests whether the json file is parsed correctly. Also tests if the IO error is raised correctly.
      Throws:
      Exception - When the test file cannot be found.

    • testGPX

      public void testGPX() throws IOException
      Tests whether the gpx file is successfully generated. Can't be tested with sample data since the generation of the gpx file uses system time. Therefore an empty set is tested.
      Throws:
      IOException - If something is wrong with the filepath.

    • verifyBbox

      public double verifyBbox​(double totalDistance, Node testNode)
      Generates a Bbox, and then returns the distance between the edge points.
      Parameters:
      totalDistance - The total distance to be walked.
      testNode - The starting point to base the Bbox on.
      Returns:
      The distance between the extremities of the bounding box.
